WEBVTT

00:00:30.045 --> 00:00:32.027
Welcome to our library studios.

00:00:32.048 --> 00:00:33.848
We're going to resume where we left off

00:00:33.889 --> 00:00:35.951
in our last program and returning to the

00:00:35.990 --> 00:00:36.310
garden.

00:00:36.331 --> 00:00:37.972
Uh, it is a, yeah,

00:00:37.993 --> 00:00:41.496
it was a story, uh, regarding, um,

00:00:41.536 --> 00:00:41.716
the

00:00:43.615 --> 00:00:46.496
fulfillment of Shabuwah that we are

00:00:46.597 --> 00:00:47.917
actually considering now.

00:00:48.258 --> 00:00:53.042
And it just happened to progress into an

00:00:53.082 --> 00:00:56.444
assessment of individuals who were trying

00:00:56.484 --> 00:00:58.344
to claim this Shabuwah harvest for

00:00:58.405 --> 00:01:01.968
themselves and disparage the one who is

00:01:02.027 --> 00:01:06.671
actually responsible for cultivating those

00:01:06.710 --> 00:01:08.632
who will be gleaned on this day.

00:01:09.572 --> 00:01:10.813
It is an interesting story.

00:01:10.953 --> 00:01:12.055
And I think that

00:01:13.424 --> 00:01:16.406
The realization that we came to about two

00:01:16.465 --> 00:01:17.846
months ago, maybe three,

00:01:18.628 --> 00:01:21.009
that the story of the garden has been

00:01:21.049 --> 00:01:25.512
misunderstood for a better part of a six

00:01:25.531 --> 00:01:26.513
thousand years,

00:01:26.572 --> 00:01:29.155
certainly in the last thirty four hundred

00:01:29.174 --> 00:01:32.637
years since the Torah has delineated that

00:01:32.736 --> 00:01:33.617
account to us.

00:01:34.237 --> 00:01:37.641
It's always assumed that an

00:01:38.248 --> 00:01:42.412
woman named Eve somehow decided,

00:01:42.632 --> 00:01:44.873
based upon being beguiled by a snake,

00:01:45.674 --> 00:01:50.278
that she would eat an apple and then

00:01:50.319 --> 00:01:52.881
she would hand it to her husband,

00:01:53.340 --> 00:01:54.602
who was named Adam.

00:01:55.662 --> 00:02:00.847
But that is both wrong and completely

00:02:00.927 --> 00:02:02.349
misses the point.

00:02:02.709 --> 00:02:04.010
You see, even before

00:02:05.495 --> 00:02:07.275
Chawah, which was her actual name.

00:02:07.396 --> 00:02:09.176
It means to express one's mind.

00:02:11.198 --> 00:02:13.859
Religious Jews will tell you it means life

00:02:13.899 --> 00:02:16.700
giver, but that would be Chaya, not Chawah.

00:02:18.421 --> 00:02:22.283
Che and Chaim is lives and Chawah means

00:02:22.324 --> 00:02:24.205
to express one's attitude.

00:02:24.884 --> 00:02:25.985
And that was her name.

00:02:28.146 --> 00:02:30.448
Long before she was even conceived,

00:02:32.038 --> 00:02:33.080
God gave up on man.

00:02:33.879 --> 00:02:36.102
And that really is the most insightful

00:02:36.122 --> 00:02:37.923
thing I can tell you about that story.

00:02:38.563 --> 00:02:39.905
Because once you understand that,

00:02:40.164 --> 00:02:43.948
you'll understand why the experiment in

00:02:43.987 --> 00:02:47.770
the garden ended and what it means for

00:02:47.889 --> 00:02:48.510
us today.

00:02:49.977 --> 00:02:50.837
You see,

00:02:51.277 --> 00:02:56.243
God told us before he gave a man

00:02:56.544 --> 00:02:58.205
a Neshama, a conscience,

00:02:58.667 --> 00:03:02.330
which is the ability to process what you

00:03:02.770 --> 00:03:07.475
observe such that you can exercise good

00:03:07.516 --> 00:03:10.199
judgment and discern right from wrong.

00:03:11.140 --> 00:03:14.784
He gave Adam this Neshama, this conscience,

00:03:15.466 --> 00:03:17.467
in addition to a nephesh soul,

00:03:17.527 --> 00:03:18.368
consciousness,

00:03:18.949 --> 00:03:21.391
when he placed him in the garden.

00:03:21.412 --> 00:03:26.137
And the garden was a protective enclosure

00:03:26.157 --> 00:03:27.598
that was conducive to life.

00:03:27.979 --> 00:03:31.201
It is a microcosm of our planet.

00:03:32.002 --> 00:03:36.009
Earth is a protective enclosure that is

00:03:36.090 --> 00:03:37.853
conducive to life.

00:03:37.992 --> 00:03:40.417
And in that, Yahowah said,

00:03:40.637 --> 00:03:42.340
even before he placed man there,

00:03:42.400 --> 00:03:45.085
that he wanted him to be observant.

00:03:46.502 --> 00:03:47.062
observant.

00:03:47.582 --> 00:03:49.524
This is shamar in Hebrew.

00:03:50.525 --> 00:03:53.046
It means to closely examine and carefully

00:03:53.106 --> 00:03:56.109
consider all that is provided for you,

00:03:56.149 --> 00:03:57.789
that is evident to you.

00:03:58.890 --> 00:04:02.013
And he then said that he wanted man

00:04:02.193 --> 00:04:03.294
to work.

00:04:05.314 --> 00:04:08.798
And to work, a shah, to engage,

00:04:08.837 --> 00:04:09.437
to act,

00:04:09.538 --> 00:04:13.040
to make a contribution such that the

00:04:15.282 --> 00:04:20.985
sum of Yahowah plus man was more than

00:04:21.285 --> 00:04:24.927
either Yahowah independently or man by

00:04:24.966 --> 00:04:25.427
himself.

00:04:27.327 --> 00:04:27.809
You see that?

00:04:28.209 --> 00:04:29.569
We're going to get to the ultimate

00:04:29.610 --> 00:04:33.291
equation that Yahowah who is one and man

00:04:33.351 --> 00:04:38.274
who is an animal created on the sixth

00:04:38.314 --> 00:04:41.315
day is known by the nomenclature of six

00:04:42.916 --> 00:04:43.096
is

00:04:44.619 --> 00:04:47.142
greater than either of them independently.

00:04:47.242 --> 00:04:48.966
Six plus one equals seven would be

00:04:48.985 --> 00:04:50.148
Yahowah's formula for this.

00:04:50.168 --> 00:04:54.033
And so these are the things that he

00:04:54.214 --> 00:04:55.637
asked of Adam.

00:04:56.718 --> 00:04:56.879
And

00:04:57.716 --> 00:04:59.918
Adam didn't deliver on either equation.

00:04:59.959 --> 00:05:03.322
He just was not particularly observant.

00:05:03.382 --> 00:05:06.225
There is nothing that would indicate he

00:05:06.264 --> 00:05:09.387
was the least bit contributory to the

00:05:09.427 --> 00:05:10.689
experience in the garden either.

00:05:11.428 --> 00:05:11.829
In fact,

00:05:12.269 --> 00:05:13.310
God was said he was a bit of

00:05:13.331 --> 00:05:16.694
a deadbeat, that he was listless,

00:05:16.793 --> 00:05:19.297
that he made no contribution.

00:05:19.336 --> 00:05:22.278
So this is the reason that God decided

00:05:22.319 --> 00:05:24.000
to end the experiment in the garden.

00:05:24.951 --> 00:05:27.473
And God even tells us that he caused

00:05:27.514 --> 00:05:28.274
the fall of man.

00:05:28.314 --> 00:05:32.216
That's a very essential lesson if you want

00:05:32.257 --> 00:05:34.338
to understand not only the garden,

00:05:34.757 --> 00:05:35.699
but where we're headed.

00:05:35.738 --> 00:05:37.660
Because in God's story,

00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:42.742
we were escorted out of the garden for

00:05:43.824 --> 00:05:48.726
failing to perform,

00:05:50.447 --> 00:05:52.949
being unobservant and listless.

00:05:53.887 --> 00:05:54.807
and being unreliable.

00:05:55.728 --> 00:05:57.088
And that was six thousand years ago,

00:05:57.329 --> 00:05:58.629
save seven.

00:05:59.610 --> 00:06:00.550
And in seven years,

00:06:00.591 --> 00:06:02.492
we're going to be allowed back into the

00:06:02.531 --> 00:06:02.732
garden.

00:06:02.752 --> 00:06:06.093
At least a select few will be given

00:06:06.112 --> 00:06:07.673
the permission to reenter the garden.

00:06:08.413 --> 00:06:10.855
So the only way you're going to know

00:06:10.875 --> 00:06:13.536
whether or not you belong in the garden

00:06:13.596 --> 00:06:15.038
going forward or whether you'll be

00:06:15.098 --> 00:06:16.899
admitted in the garden going forward,

00:06:16.918 --> 00:06:19.201
or you can even be among those who

00:06:19.261 --> 00:06:21.721
will be put to work helping those who

00:06:22.403 --> 00:06:23.923
are admitted into the garden,

00:06:24.543 --> 00:06:26.706
is to know what happened in the garden

00:06:26.805 --> 00:06:28.187
and what went wrong.

00:06:28.567 --> 00:06:29.987
And that's the analysis that I have

00:06:30.028 --> 00:06:33.389
provided here quite recently in the Yahowah

00:06:33.410 --> 00:06:35.331
blog so that you would know what went

00:06:35.372 --> 00:06:35.552
wrong.

00:06:37.593 --> 00:06:40.394
So I'm telling you that long before Chawah

00:06:40.415 --> 00:06:44.757
was even conceived, God gave up on man.

00:06:44.896 --> 00:06:48.617
And the testimony that God provides is

00:06:48.658 --> 00:06:51.238
that he caused the fall of man.

00:06:51.358 --> 00:06:56.021
And the reason he did so was,

00:06:56.060 --> 00:06:56.901
of course, twofold.

00:06:57.100 --> 00:06:58.622
One is that he wanted peace.

00:06:59.790 --> 00:07:00.971
the man to be observant.

00:07:01.490 --> 00:07:03.812
He wanted the man to engage and make

00:07:03.831 --> 00:07:04.711
a contribution.

00:07:05.233 --> 00:07:07.793
He wanted the man to demonstrate that he

00:07:07.834 --> 00:07:10.894
could listen and respond and then show

00:07:10.935 --> 00:07:12.795
that he was reliable so that if he

00:07:12.855 --> 00:07:13.656
made a mistake,

00:07:14.096 --> 00:07:16.918
he would correct it and move on learning

00:07:16.978 --> 00:07:17.278
from it.

00:07:17.358 --> 00:07:20.379
And that if he tripped and fell,

00:07:20.819 --> 00:07:21.759
he'd stand back up.

00:07:22.440 --> 00:07:26.682
These are requirements to A,

00:07:26.882 --> 00:07:28.204
garner Yahowah's attention,

00:07:29.264 --> 00:07:29.764
And B,

00:07:29.843 --> 00:07:32.625
be left off this planet so that we

00:07:32.665 --> 00:07:35.026
can explore the universe with our God.

00:07:37.206 --> 00:07:39.947
So these are the things that caused God

00:07:39.987 --> 00:07:41.247
to give up on Adam.

00:07:41.267 --> 00:07:41.728
And you say, well,

00:07:41.747 --> 00:07:42.788
why didn't he just give him more time?

00:07:42.827 --> 00:07:42.987
Well,

00:07:43.528 --> 00:07:45.108
because of the fact that he was in

00:07:45.249 --> 00:07:47.589
such a cloistered environment,

00:07:47.649 --> 00:07:50.190
such a sheltered, protective environment,

00:07:50.571 --> 00:07:53.091
there was no incentive for Adam to

00:07:53.151 --> 00:07:53.591
improve.

00:07:54.492 --> 00:07:55.793
He was given all the food he needed,

00:07:55.833 --> 00:07:56.733
didn't need to work for it.

00:07:57.440 --> 00:07:58.925
So why engage?

00:07:58.966 --> 00:07:59.767
Why do anything?

00:08:00.249 --> 00:08:01.372
He was

00:08:03.117 --> 00:08:04.517
completely protected,

00:08:04.557 --> 00:08:07.500
so there was no outside source of stimuli

00:08:07.540 --> 00:08:11.204
that he had to raise up against to

00:08:12.565 --> 00:08:13.146
overcome,

00:08:13.567 --> 00:08:14.788
so he was never going to develop any

00:08:14.848 --> 00:08:15.288
character.

00:08:16.589 --> 00:08:16.769
You know,

00:08:16.790 --> 00:08:18.370
he was seeing the same things every day,

00:08:18.451 --> 00:08:20.213
so what was going to be new to

00:08:20.312 --> 00:08:21.995
observe that was going to change that,

00:08:22.074 --> 00:08:25.538
and what God had perceived is that when

00:08:26.399 --> 00:08:26.980
he's wrong,

00:08:27.040 --> 00:08:27.259
he'd

00:08:28.324 --> 00:08:29.507
doesn't correct himself.

00:08:29.547 --> 00:08:30.829
He doesn't learn from the mistake.

00:08:31.211 --> 00:08:31.791
When falling,

00:08:31.831 --> 00:08:34.897
he wallows in his shame and doesn't get

00:08:34.957 --> 00:08:36.299
up.

00:08:36.320 --> 00:08:38.062
That he felt he was entitled.

00:08:38.323 --> 00:08:40.508
He's kind of like Generation Z.

00:08:42.559 --> 00:08:44.802
So God recognized in that environment,

00:08:45.302 --> 00:08:47.745
it would be just like washing a goldfish,

00:08:47.765 --> 00:08:48.405
swimming a bowl,

00:08:49.226 --> 00:08:51.249
and it was never going to change.

00:08:51.789 --> 00:08:53.611
So he ended the experiment in the garden.

00:08:53.851 --> 00:08:58.015
And because God is sympathetic and he had

00:08:58.056 --> 00:09:00.379
created this man for a purpose,

00:09:00.479 --> 00:09:01.899
even though it had not worked out,

00:09:02.520 --> 00:09:03.721
he didn't want man to be alone.

00:09:04.423 --> 00:09:07.364
So what that tells you is that God

00:09:07.384 --> 00:09:09.984
had already made the decision to leave the

00:09:10.104 --> 00:09:12.804
man prior to creating the woman,

00:09:13.105 --> 00:09:14.184
or he would not have said it that

00:09:14.225 --> 00:09:15.686
way, would he?

00:09:16.385 --> 00:09:19.986
And so he created the woman for an

00:09:20.027 --> 00:09:22.366
express purpose, to be helpful to the man.

00:09:23.246 --> 00:09:25.467
And she was not.

00:09:25.587 --> 00:09:28.129
She was actually the opposite of helpful.

00:09:28.288 --> 00:09:31.269
And there's a story of a woman who

00:09:31.408 --> 00:09:33.090
was once involved with...

00:09:34.285 --> 00:09:35.734
this mission who was

00:09:37.149 --> 00:09:38.071
counterproductive as well,

00:09:38.150 --> 00:09:39.412
who could not be trusted, who,

00:09:39.491 --> 00:09:40.613
when making a mistake,

00:09:41.352 --> 00:09:44.436
could not learn from it, and when tripped,

00:09:45.576 --> 00:09:46.917
stayed in a fallen state.

00:09:47.177 --> 00:09:49.379
And she is embodied,

00:09:49.740 --> 00:09:52.140
and all we can learn about Chawah,

00:09:52.402 --> 00:09:53.302
she represents,

00:09:53.361 --> 00:09:55.703
and that's why God is going to use

00:09:55.744 --> 00:09:59.326
this occasion that we're on now to speak

00:09:59.366 --> 00:10:00.508
about her prophetically,

00:10:01.008 --> 00:10:02.850
and God's really upset with her,

00:10:03.730 --> 00:10:05.410
and those who are part of her company.

00:10:06.272 --> 00:10:09.432
so what we find is that uh after

00:10:09.472 --> 00:10:13.134
god ended the experience in the garden and

00:10:13.195 --> 00:10:16.056
he set out terms and conditions for man

00:10:16.096 --> 00:10:20.437
to to then develop outside of it that

00:10:20.956 --> 00:10:24.298
it went very poorly in a hurry and

00:10:24.818 --> 00:10:27.659
and it was that all man with a

00:10:28.220 --> 00:10:30.821
Neshama with a conscience fell

00:10:32.229 --> 00:10:34.210
The term Naphilylym,

00:10:34.370 --> 00:10:37.650
which is errantly rendered giants in

00:10:37.770 --> 00:10:40.131
almost every translation,

00:10:40.451 --> 00:10:41.591
does not mean giants.

00:10:41.971 --> 00:10:43.852
In fact, it's the opposite of giants.

00:10:44.653 --> 00:10:46.793
Nephal, from which it is the plural of,

00:10:46.874 --> 00:10:47.634
Naphilylym,

00:10:47.974 --> 00:10:49.653
would be the plural of nephal in Hebrew.

00:10:50.335 --> 00:10:51.674
It means they were the fallen.

00:10:52.754 --> 00:10:55.375
Just as God caused the fall of man,

00:10:56.076 --> 00:10:59.957
man outside of the garden with a Neshama

00:11:00.697 --> 00:11:01.518
fell down.

00:11:01.905 --> 00:11:02.765
precipitously.

00:11:03.725 --> 00:11:07.947
And so God wanted to get a fresh

00:11:07.967 --> 00:11:10.008
start because he regretted even creating

00:11:10.048 --> 00:11:10.327
man.

00:11:10.827 --> 00:11:12.369
We were rotten to the core.

00:11:13.149 --> 00:11:16.830
We used our ability to think to harm

00:11:16.870 --> 00:11:18.429
people, to be hurtful.

00:11:19.230 --> 00:11:22.932
And so this is the story that developed

00:11:23.052 --> 00:11:24.552
and it really never changed.

00:11:25.011 --> 00:11:29.714
And so God is providing humanity with six

00:11:29.734 --> 00:11:31.193
thousand years to get our act together.

00:11:33.192 --> 00:11:36.053
with enormous amounts of revelation so

00:11:36.134 --> 00:11:40.375
that he can communicate to us in such

00:11:40.416 --> 00:11:42.836
a way that we understand what he is

00:11:42.917 --> 00:11:45.278
offering and what he's expecting in return

00:11:45.818 --> 00:11:47.460
and how we are to engage with him.

00:11:48.059 --> 00:11:49.140
And along the way,

00:11:49.160 --> 00:11:52.121
the greatest exemplar happens to be David,

00:11:53.062 --> 00:11:56.063
who mankind has treated more reprehensibly

00:11:56.083 --> 00:11:57.384
than anyone who has ever lived.

00:11:58.427 --> 00:11:59.207
You see,

00:11:59.227 --> 00:12:02.090
the whole lie of Judaism and Christianity

00:12:02.149 --> 00:12:05.974
are based almost exclusively on Robin

00:12:06.014 --> 00:12:09.976
Dowd, who is the exemplar of our lives.

00:12:10.017 --> 00:12:15.782
He is the one whose attitude and aptitude

00:12:16.842 --> 00:12:21.726
earned him the love of our creator,

00:12:22.268 --> 00:12:24.048
because he was all things that Adam was

00:12:24.109 --> 00:12:24.328
not.

00:12:25.110 --> 00:12:25.931
You see, Dowd was...

00:12:27.469 --> 00:12:28.009
engaged.

00:12:28.369 --> 00:12:29.168
He was observant.

00:12:29.889 --> 00:12:30.850
He was thoughtful.

00:12:31.929 --> 00:12:33.090
He listened.

00:12:34.010 --> 00:12:34.990
When he made a mistake,

00:12:35.051 --> 00:12:37.692
he learned from it and grew as a

00:12:37.751 --> 00:12:38.172
result.

00:12:38.511 --> 00:12:39.631
When he tripped and fell,

00:12:39.692 --> 00:12:40.611
he got back up.

00:12:41.513 --> 00:12:44.734
He was passionate and his zealousness for

00:12:44.754 --> 00:12:46.813
the relationship that he had developed

00:12:46.854 --> 00:12:47.494
with Yahowah.

00:12:48.214 --> 00:12:49.894
And so Dowd is

00:12:51.158 --> 00:12:52.719
the exemplar of what God's looking for.

00:12:52.759 --> 00:12:54.379
He was Shezak, tough.

00:12:54.880 --> 00:12:57.121
He was a great defender of Israel.

00:12:58.003 --> 00:13:02.326
He was the ultimate student of the Torah,

00:13:02.365 --> 00:13:05.528
having written both a summary form

00:13:05.648 --> 00:13:06.467
expression of it,

00:13:06.768 --> 00:13:08.229
as well as the hundred and nineteenth

00:13:08.249 --> 00:13:10.490
Psalm, which is the longest by far,

00:13:10.551 --> 00:13:13.153
which is a comprehensive analysis of how

00:13:13.192 --> 00:13:14.494
we are to observe the Torah.

00:13:15.432 --> 00:13:17.434
And it is through Dowd that Yahowah

00:13:17.674 --> 00:13:19.917
fulfilled the Mowedym, Pisach, Matzah,

00:13:19.937 --> 00:13:20.337
Bikuwrym.

00:13:23.513 --> 00:13:25.634
the spring Miqraey in thirty-three CE,

00:13:25.673 --> 00:13:26.894
year four thousand YAH.

00:13:27.413 --> 00:13:28.575
And yet in Christianity,

00:13:29.034 --> 00:13:29.955
everything Dowd did,

00:13:29.995 --> 00:13:31.836
including being crucified to fulfill

00:13:32.275 --> 00:13:34.037
Pesach in his second of third lives,

00:13:34.096 --> 00:13:37.298
was stolen by the mythical construct of

00:13:37.437 --> 00:13:40.058
Jesus, as well as Dowd's title.

00:13:40.099 --> 00:13:42.039
Son of God and Messiah are titles that

00:13:42.059 --> 00:13:43.900
belong to Dowd and to no one else

00:13:44.061 --> 00:13:44.860
other than Dowd.

